# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# cache-as-thermodynamic-substrate.form — the build/runtime cache is a
#                                          region of the substrate, not a
#                                          pile of files beside it
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The cache is the same physics the lattice already runs. Every cached artifact —
# a source-compiled prelude, a flattened fourth-arm table, a JIT plan, a name
# resolution, a recipe-walk result — is a CELL with a thermodynamic STATE
# (substrate-thermodynamics.form). What is new here is not a mechanism; it is the
# recognition that the cache was never outside the body.
#
# RUNNABLE, four-way: form-stdlib/cache-phase.fk + tests/cache-phase-band.fk
# (verdict 255 on Go, Rust, TypeScript, and fkwu — fourth-arm-bands.txt: cache-phase).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The two facets — why a cache cell is more than a phase cell
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A cache cell carries two facets the lattice's pure-phase cell does not split:
#
#   IDENTITY     — key + input-hash + measurements. Cheap. ALWAYS kept.
#   MATERIALIZED — the expensive artifact bytes. Droppable. Re-derivable.
#
# The whole "trust the cache, don't wipe it" ask lives in that split:
#
#   TRUST  is input-hash equality, not freshness. A content-addressed key means a
#          re-derived value is PROVABLY the same value. mtime is irrelevant; a cache
#          entry is trustworthy exactly when its input-hash still matches the inputs,
#          whether it is frozen-materialized or sublimated to a bare index. So we do
#          not wipe on suspicion — we only recompute on a hash MISMATCH.
#
#   DON'T-WIPE  is the substrate conservation law (substrate-thermodynamics.form:
#          "SUBLIMATE removes NOTHING — NodeID and kind persist; re-coherable").
#          Going cold does not delete the entry. It SUBLIMATES: release the bytes,
#          keep the identity. The index — key, input-hash, measurements — survives in
#          gas. Re-request re-materializes (CONDENSE) under the same key+hash. We
#          never lose the trust-metadata, so we never have a reason to distrust the
#          whole cache and clear it. Every `rm -rf .cache` this body has ever run was
#          the crude, lossy version of sublimate.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The measurement → state map (cache reads the same three counts)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   hits       — reads since birth          -> degree      (circulation)
#   recomputes — times it had to regenerate  -> churn        (temperature)
#   shared     — distinct callers of its shape -> population (pressure)
#
# state-of a cache cell is phase-state over (hits, recomputes) with the same
# hysteresis gap (ice-degree > gas-degree) that keeps the lattice from thrashing.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The four transitions, with cache meaning  (cache-phase.fk makes these run)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   FREEZE     water -> ice : PIN durable. Hot, settled, trusted — never evict; persist
#                             past process exit, share across machines by content-hash.
#   SUBLIMATE  ice -> gas   : RELEASE the bytes, KEEP the index. The "don't wipe."
#   CONDENSE   gas -> water : RE-MATERIALIZE a cold index that got re-requested, under
#                             the same key+hash (re-coherable; trust preserved).
#   MELT       ice -> water : RECOMPUTE. Still hot, but the inputs changed (hash
#                             mismatch) — the one honest reason to regenerate.
#
# phase-invite over a cache cell IS "what wants to move where." Run it report-only
# first (show the 3×3 of cache cells by layer × state) before any eviction acts.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The layers, today — what is already trustworthy, what is mtime-blind
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each is a population of cache cells. The key scheme decides whether the layer can be
# TRUSTED (content-addressed) or only GUESSED-AT (mtime). Content-addressed layers are
# already safe to keep across machines; mtime layers are the ones we keep wiping.
#
#   source-compiled  (.cache/source-compiled/)  content-hash(source) + compiler-chain
#                                                hash → already trustworthy.
#   fourth-arm tables (.cache/fourth/t-*.txt)    content-hash(band-sources + chain) →
#                                                trustworthy; today composted by mtime
#                                                (-mtime +14 -delete) — that delete is a
#                                                lossy sublimate that drops the index too.
#   fourth-arm binary (.cache/fourth/fkwu-*)     content-hash(emitter chain + GO_BIN) →
#                                                trustworthy.
#   TS bundle (form-kernel-ts/dist/main.mjs)     mtime(src/*.ts) → mtime-blind; a touch
#                                                with no content change forces a rebuild.
#
# The lift each layer asks for: emit its three counts as a cache cell, let phase-invite
# choose freeze/sublimate/condense/melt, and replace `-mtime +N -delete` with SUBLIMATE
# (drop bytes, keep the content-hash index). Then the cache is trusted by hash and
# pruned by physics, and wiping becomes a thing we no longer reach for.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Form-native access — why the cache must be a substrate citizen
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A caching strategy that cannot read its own cache is a strategy written blind. Once a
# cache entry is a record cell (cache-phase.fk: key/hash/hits/recomputes/materialized),
# the strategy is itself a Form recipe over cache metadata — and so is every OTHER
# recipe the branching and learning primitives choose:
#
#   CHOOSE       recipe-branching-sense.form / recipe-choice-runtime.fk — at a cache
#                fork (serve the materialized value vs recompute), `choose` branches on
#                the cell's state and trust; the cache cell IS the evidence the choice
#                point reads.
#   LEARN        choice-outcome-learning.fk / choice-receipt.fk — a hit that saved real
#                work rewards FREEZE; a recompute that was cheap teaches "this was not
#                worth materializing." The cache's measurements ARE the reward signal.
#   SAME PHYSICS learned-primitive.fk — heat lifting a hot composite into a callable
#                primitive is freeze on the RECIPE population; a learned primitive that
#                cools dissolves (sublimate). The cache is the same metabolism on the
#                ARTIFACT population. One physics, two populations.
#
# So the cache metadata is not a side channel. It is the observability the choice and
# learning primitives already want, expressed as cells they can already read.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Grounded, and what is design
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GROUNDED (runs four-way today): the metabolism itself — cache-state, cache-invite,
# cache-trustworthy?, and the identity-conserving transitions (sublimate / condense /
# remelt) — proven in form-stdlib/cache-phase.fk against tests/cache-phase-band.fk,
# verdict 255 on all four arms.
#
# DESIGN (the next honest steps, taken only as need calls):
#   1. Each cache layer emits its (hits, recomputes, shared) as a cache cell — start
#      with the fourth-arm tables, whose ~100s warm pre-scan and mtime-delete are the
#      live friction.
#   2. Replace `-mtime +N -delete` with phase-driven SUBLIMATE: drop bytes, keep the
#      content-hash index. Re-request CONDENSEs. The cache stops being wiped.
#   3. The TS bundle (and any other mtime-keyed layer) moves to a content-hash key, so
#      "trustworthy" stops meaning "freshly built on this machine."
#   4. Cache MORE layers — JIT plans, name resolutions, recipe-walk results — each a
#      cell in whatever state its counts put it; gas, water, or ice, by the same map.
#
# Companions:
#   substrate-thermodynamics.form       — the state axis + conservation law this rests on
#   form-stdlib/substrate-phase.fk      — the runnable phase metabolism it composes with
#   form-stdlib/learned-primitive.fk    — the same physics on the recipe population
#   form-stdlib/cache-phase.fk          — the RUNNABLE cache metabolism (four-way)
#   recipe-branching-sense.form         — the choice primitive that reads cache cells
#   form-stdlib/cache.fk                — one carrier (parsed-recipe on-disk cache) to lift
